<h3 id="2-here-and-now-revisited">2. here and now (revisited)</h3>
<p>As a member of <a href="http://david-ryan.co.uk/">David Ryan</a>â€™s <a href="https://operaapertaproject.com/">Opera Aperta Project</a>, I have been designing an alternative version of of â€˜<a href="https://operaapertaproject.com/works/">Here and Now</a>â€™ (2020) in which I develop sound textures to be used as control parameters of sound in a generative soundscape. The sound textures are based on recordings prepared for the original piece (e.g. bass clarinet, percussion, Tibetan bowls, cello, piano, voices). In regard to form, the soundscape generator for â€˜here and now (revisited)â€™ is similar to the Shamanic Soundscape Generator. It has two main groups of audio tracks. One that is more controlled (e.g. overall duration) and one in which a variety of sound textures interact with real-time EEG via a neurofeedback protocol. The goal of the experiment is to create a piece is to demonstrate the use of BCMI for audiences primarily interested in contemporary classical music.</p>

